px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقد قال تعالى: \" ومن قدر عليه رزقه فلينفق مما آتاه الله \" قيل معناه: ليبع أحد ثوبيه. وقيل معناه: فليستقرض بجاهه، فذلك مما آتاه الله.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, the Most High has said: \"And whoever is constrained in his provision, let him spend from what God has given him [mā ātāhu Allāh].\" It is said its meaning is: let him sell one of his two garments. And it is said its meaning is: let him borrow on the strength of his standing [bijahih], for that is from what God has given him [mā ātāhu Allāh].\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"8":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0.5","c":"وَكَأَيِّنْ","d":"nِّyَaʾَkَw","e":"nِّyَaʾَkَw"},{"b":"1.0","h":"2.98","c":"مِنْ","d":"nِّm","e":"nِّm"},{"b":"2.5","h":"3.8","c":"قَرْيَةٍ","d":"ٍẗَyْrَq","e":"ٍẗَyْrَq"},{"b":"3.4","h":"5.42","c":"عَتَتْ","d":"ْtَtَʿع","e":"ْtَtَʿع"},{"b":"4.0","h":"6.45","c":"عَنْ","d":"ْnَʿع","e":"ْnَʿع"},{"b":"4.4","h":"7.13","c":"أَمْرِ","d":"ِrْmَaʾ","e":"ِrْmَaʾ"},{"b":"5.0","h":"8.07","c":"رَبِّهَا","d":"āَhِّbَr","e":"āَhِّbَr"},{"b":"6.0","h":"9.83","c":"وَرُسُلِهِ","d":"ۦِhِlُsُrَw","e":"ۦِhِlُsُrَw"},{"b":"7.1","h":"11.68","c":"فَحَاسَبْنَاهَا","d":"āَhَٰnْbَsāَḥَf","e":"āَhَٰnْbَsāَḥَf"},{"b":"8.8","h":"14.89","c":"حِسَابًا","d":"āًbāَsِḥ","e":"āًbāَsِḥ"},{"b":"10.3","h":"17.01","c":"شَدِيدًا","d":"āًdyِdَhs","e":"āًdyِdَhs"},{"b":"16.0","h":"19.05","c":"وَعَذَّبْنَاهَا","d":"āَhَٰnْbَّhdَʿعَw","e":"āَhَٰnْbَّhdَʿعَw"},{"b":"18.5","h":"21.95","c":"عَذَابًا","d":"āًbāَhdَʿع","e":"āًbāَhdَʿع"},{"b":"19.3","h":"23.44","c":"نُكْرًا","d":"āًrْkُّn","e":"āًrْkُّn"}],"