 seven heavens, and from the earth their like. The Command [al-amr] descends between them, that you may know that Allah is over all things competent and that Allah has encompassed all things in knowledge.\" And these are matters whose true interpretation [ta'wil] none knows except Allah and those firmly rooted in knowledge [al-rasikhun fi al-'ilm]. And Ibn 'Abbas, may Allah be pleased with them both, expressed the exclusive possession by those firmly rooted in knowledge [al-rasikhun fi al-'ilm] of sciences [ulum] which the understandings of creation cannot bear, when he recited the saying of the Exalted: \"The Command [al-amr] descends between them,\" and said: \"If I mentioned what I know of the meaning of this verse, you would stone me.\" And in another wording: \"You would say, 'He is an unbeliever.'\"\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}}}